        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Positioning in Breast MR Imaging to Optimize Image Quality" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Eren D.  Yeh" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Dianne  Georgian-Smith" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Sughra  Raza" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Lisa  Bussolari" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jacqueline  Pawlisz-Hoff" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Robyn L.  Birdwell" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="The authors provide a guide to recognizing common artifacts that result from improper positioning for breast MR imaging and suggest ways to avoid such artifacts so that imaging can be optimized for..." /><meta name="Description" content="The authors provide a guide to recognizing common artifacts that result from improper positioning for breast MR imaging and suggest ways to avoid such artifacts so that imaging can be optimized for..." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Improper positioning of the breasts in a dedicated breast coil causes inhomogeneous fat saturation as well as other artifacts that decrease the sensitivity of breast magnetic resonance imaging. Imp..." /><meta name="Description" content="Improper positioning of the breasts in a dedicated breast coil causes inhomogeneous fat saturation as well as other artifacts that decrease the sensitivity of breast magnetic resonance imaging. Imp..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2014-01-01" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="125193" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.341125193" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.341125193" /><meta name="dc.Language" content="EN" /><meta 